title: Tom and (Y/N)'s New Year
body:
🎉🎉🎉

• (Y/N) and Tom would love spending New Year’s together. This was their first New year’s as a married couple and it was going to be special.

• Tom would plan to fly (Y/N) to LA to celebrate the new year at (Y/N)’s parents house. She’d be so happy and it’d be emotional.

• Her family threw a house party with not that many people, mostly family and close friends.

• Tom’s family were on vacation, which was sad but they’d still FaceTime them at midnight. They’d have a blast on vacation though.

• (Y/N)’s mom would make so many different things and it’d be so much fun.

• One of (Y/N)’s cousins was a DJ in the backyard and it would be like being at a club.

• A lot of cute Snapchat and Instagram stories of (Y/N) and her family members and friends. Also, of course with Tom, the internet would go crazy when the two of them took a selfie or someone else took a picture for them.

• (Y/N) was wearing a long sleeveed black over the shoulder dress with heels and a red lip. Tom was gushing over her all night and everyone teased him at points and (Y/N) found it so funny.

• Tom would take so many pictures and little cute videos of his wife and post them on his story with the cutest captions. The internet would melt. 😭

• And we can’t forget about New year’s kiss, Tom would be holding, (Y/N) so close to him as everyone would countdown. As soon as the crowd shouted happy new year he’d kiss his wife and it’d be so sweet and passionate.

blog.description: Sent from my iPhone

body:
About that Vegan food…

I’ve been mulling on that little Pic from Chanterelle, Benedict’s nutritionist. And I have some lingering questions:

1. Why was the vast majority of the food labeled for Zero? If they live together and both use her, why would the majority be marked for Zero, with only a few marked Ben?

2. I thought Benedict says he cooks his own food? Why would he use this kind of service if he cooks his own food? (Or is that why we only see a few things for him, vs Zero?…but then that means that he doesn’t cook for his wife!)

3. Now this one is the question that just won’t go away: if Chanterelle is cooking for BOTH of them, why is that the meals are individually labeled? I mean, I get that one may like certain foods more or have an allergy, etc., but still. Not only that, but why is that Zero (when we’ve gotten a look at her), looks much healthier than before, yet Benedict looks worse? Furthermore, why does he seem to look better when he’s out of the country for a bit than he does when he’s eating these pre-made, custom meals?


Maybe it’s not the Vegan diet, itself that is bad for him? Maybe it’s just the prepackaged meals from Chanterelle? And I wonder why that would be…maybe I’ve been watching too much Discovery ID or reading too much CDAN (see the Omarosa blinds)…

I don’t have her 100% down yet, but some of her powers are that she can jump super extra high, even for a Spider-person, and she has a distraction/confusion move where she starts flashing bright, blinding colors.

She likes turning her webbing into forts and hammocks, and when Vine was a thing, she did dorky dances on Vine regularly.

body:
Pairing: MC!Tattoo Artist!Peter Parker x Barton!Reader

Warning: Angst. Revenge. Swearing. Lust. Jealousy. Snarkiness. Overprotectiveness. Pinning. Mild Cheating. Guilt. Anger. Confusion.

A/N: Look this is more gritty, dirty and adult than I have wrote, but I’m excited about this. There is a mild moment of cheating and no it’s not condoned. Just know if you aren’t for that moment, don’t ask to be tagged.

[Synopsis Has Been Removed]

Tag List Is Open!!

Peter Parker

He jogs into the clubhouse, his jaw still clenched. He finds Clint, standing off to one side with Harold, Tony, Buck, and Nat. He hurries towards them, Clint looks relieved when he notices him.

“Sorry, I’m here.” He shoves a hand through his hair.

“What took you so long?” Tony looks over at him. His jaw ticks.

“Had to put an end to things with MJ.” He mutters, with disgust.

“What?” Clint’s eyes grow wide.

“Thank god.” Nat smirks, folding her arms over her chest.

“Finally.” Harold grins.

“Damn right.” Tony shakes his head slowly.

“You good?” Buck smirks at him.

“I know, what happened to Y/N.” He glances at Buck then to Clint.

“What? What happened?” Clint’s hand closes on Peter’s arm, pleading with him.

“First, to understand you have to know something.” He nods, Buck nods softly. “Clint, you’re my best friend, have been for ninety percent of our lives, but during Y/N’s senior year we were dating.” He swallows. Clint’s mouth opens but he cuts him off. “Not just dating, I’ve been in love with your sister since we were kids. I’m hopelessly, irrationally, in love with your sister. I’m the reason she left college, and why she’s running now.” He sighs, his chest tightening, waiting for Clint to punch him in the jaw. Clint’s hand comes up fast and in full swing. It slams open palm into the side of his head. He winces leaning back, looking confused at Clint.

“It took you this long to admit that?” He scuffs, shaking his head.

“Wait, you knew?” Peter’s stomach plummets. Confusion wrecks his body.

“We all did.” Harold smirks.

“Seriously?” Peter stares at them.

“I saw you pick her up one night.” Harold chuckles.

“Mom saw you kissing her in your truck one night.” Clint nods.

“That’s how you knew?” Peter looks at his best friend.

“I knew long before you two started sneaking around.” Clint smirks at him. He was completely mind blown, this whole time the one person they thought stood in their way, knew. Since the very beginning.

“Time for this later, boys.” Tony looks around.

“Right.” Peter nods scratching the back of his head. “Well MJ confessed to me tonight that she tried to pay Y/N to leave town and when she refused, MJ blackmailed her, and she agreed to leave town.” Peter nods.

“Why?” Harold growls. Y/N was his only daughter, he and Clint were always overly protective of her.

“With what?” Clint’s voice is hard.

“So I would stop loving her and we could be happy again.” He shakes his head. “Vegas.” He grinds out.

“Fuck.” Buck breathes, stunned, like Clint.

“Prissy Cunt.” Nat mutters, her lips curl.

“Dad.” Clint turns quickly as if something just came to him. “Don’t you still have the same clause on Y/N credit card? It’s the same card she’s had since she was a teen. Do you think, you could call and find out her charges?” Everyone exchanges a look.

“Fuck that.” Tony grins. “Declare that bitch stolen.” A cocky smirk turns up his lips.

“You’re a fucking genius.” Clint grins, pulling out his phone.

“I could kiss you old man.” He points at Tony.

“Let the red head, she’s cuter.” Tony chuckles. Nat winks at him.

“Hello, yes. I need to report my sister’s card stolen.” Clint nods, phone to his ear.





“She checked into a hotel on the other side of town, forty-five minutes ago.” Clint shoves his phone back into his pocket.

“Why a hotel?” Peter’s brow pulls down.

“Where is she going?” Harold looks around.

“Vegas.” Buck mutters. Realization dawns on Clint and Peter.

“Over my dead body.” He growls, heading for the door. Clint right on his heels, the others hurrying after them.

“Do we want to know about Vegas?” Harold asks as Clint unlocks the doors to his Four Runner.

“No.” Clint, Bucky and Peter grumble, everyone piling in. They’re speeding out of the clubhouse parking lot moments later.

“So you ended it with MJ?” Clint asks after several long minutes of silence. Nat and Bucky sat in the hatch, leaving Harold and Tony in the backseat.

“I don’t love her.” He sighs. “Besides, she cheated on me at her bachelorette party, and blackmailed your sister into leaving town. I couldn’t ever forgive her for that alone, I can’t marry her.” He shrugs a shoulder, looking out the window.

“You know when Y/N was graduating, I figured one of you was going to come clean.” Clint smirks, eyes on the road, as Peter looks over at him. “Then she said she wanted to go to Duke. I thought for damn sure your ass was going to go with her.” He nods slowly. “But I heard her crying that night, and you texted me about Felicia. I figured you two had a fight or something. You’d make up and come clean. Till we got those letters.” He sighs.

“I was trying to find away to tell you.” He admits. “I was going to beg her to stay here, to stay with me. Till Felicia came along ruining everything. She told Y/N I cheated. There was nobody but your sister, Clint. Nobody, still isn’t anyone else.” He shrugs, glancing out the window again.

“Well obviously, you picked her over the woman you were marrying.” Clint laughs, several chuckles come from the back of the truck.

“She isn’t Y/N.” He sighs, dropping his head back against the head rest. “Since she’s been back, I’ve been drowning like I’m eighteen again and dying for the smallest contact from her.” He smirks in the dark.

“I planned to object at your wedding.” Clint laughs. Peter’s head snaps over stunned.

“What?” He laughs.

“Me too.” Buck calls from the backseat. He looks back at them.

“Same.” Nat smirks.

“We planned to drug and kidnap you.” Tony jerks a thumb at Harold who nods.

“Yup.” He grins.

“So you all had a plan?” He looks back at Clint who laughs.

“Oh yeah we all had one. From the night of your bachelor party.” Clint snorts.

“You weren’t very subtle.” Buck laughs.

“He never was! Not once in his life when it came to my little sister was he ever subtle or smooth.” Clint cracks up.

“I mean, I got your sister.” Peter shrugs, grinning.

“That’s not saying much. Look what her mom settled for.” Tony laughs.

“Damn dad you going to take that?” Clint laughs. Peter’s cracking up in the passenger seat.

“Hey, he can say what he wants. I still got your mom.” Harold chuckles, a cocky smirk on his lips.

“This family is so fucking weird.” Clint shakes his head.

“Hey that’s the hotel.” Peter pats the dash pointing with his other hand.

“What’s the plan?” Nat asks as they all pile out.

“Who needs a plan?” Peter looks at her funny.

“Oh, okay.” She nods slowly.

“Told you. Never smooth or subtle.” Clint whispers. He gives Clint’s shoulder a shove, before he heads for the door. He heads for the front desk.

“How can I help you?” She smiles.

“A woman checked in here, with a card, under the name of Y/N Barton.” He nods.

“She’s my sister. We’re just worried about her. She took off without a word and her phones off.” Clint flashes his ID and a grin at her.

“Sure. She’s in room 217. Elevator to the right, second floor and go left.” She directs them with a smile.

“Thanks.” Clint winks at her, Peter sighs shaking his head.

“It’s like taking Tony out.” He mutters, pushing Clint towards the elevator.

“Sorry, I’m here.” He shoves a hand through his hair.

“What took you so long?” Tony looks over at him. His jaw ticks.

“Had to put an end to things with MJ.” He mutters, with disgust.

“What?” Clint’s eyes grow wide.

“Thank god.” Nat smirks, folding her arms over her chest.

“Finally.” Harold grins.

“Damn right.” Tony shakes his head slowly.

“You good?” Buck smirks at him.

“I know, what happened to Y/N.” He glances at Buck then to Clint.

“What? What happened?” Clint’s hand closes on Peter’s arm, pleading with him.

“First, to understand you have to know something.” He nods, Buck nods softly. “Clint, you’re my best friend, have been for ninety percent of our lives, but during Y/N’s senior year we were dating.” He swallows. Clint’s mouth opens but he cuts him off. “Not just dating, I’ve been in love with your sister since we were kids. I’m hopelessly, irrationally, in love with your sister. I’m the reason she left college, and why she’s running now.” He sighs, his chest tightening, waiting for Clint to punch him in the jaw. Clint’s hand comes up fast and in full swing. It slams open palm into the side of his head. He winces leaning back, looking confused at Clint.

“It took you this long to admit that?” He scuffs, shaking his head.

“Wait, you knew?” Peter’s stomach plummets. Confusion wrecks his body.

“We all did.” Harold smirks.

“Seriously?” Peter stares at them.

“I saw you pick her up one night.” Harold chuckles.

“Mom saw you kissing her in your truck one night.” Clint nods.

“That’s how you knew?” Peter looks at his best friend.

“I knew long before you two started sneaking around.” Clint smirks at him. He was completely mind blown, this whole time the one person they thought stood in their way, knew. Since the very beginning.

“Time for this later, boys.” Tony looks around.

“Right.” Peter nods scratching the back of his head. “Well MJ confessed to me tonight that she tried to pay Y/N to leave town and when she refused, MJ blackmailed her, and she agreed to leave town.” Peter nods.

“Why?” Harold growls. Y/N was his only daughter, he and Clint were always overly protective of her.

“With what?” Clint’s voice is hard.

“So I would stop loving her and we could be happy again.” He shakes his head. “Vegas.” He grinds out.

“Fuck.” Buck breathes, stunned, like Clint.

“Prissy Cunt.” Nat mutters, her lips curl.

“Dad.” Clint turns quickly as if something just came to him. “Don’t you still have the same clause on Y/N credit card? It’s the same card she’s had since she was a teen. Do you think, you could call and find out her charges?” Everyone exchanges a look.

“Fuck that.” Tony grins. “Declare that bitch stolen.” A cocky smirk turns up his lips.

“You’re a fucking genius.” Clint grins, pulling out his phone.

“I could kiss you old man.” He points at Tony.

“Let the red head, she’s cuter.” Tony chuckles. Nat winks at him.

“Hello, yes. I need to report my sister’s card stolen.” Clint nods, phone to his ear.





“She checked into a hotel on the other side of town, forty-five minutes ago.” Clint shoves his phone back into his pocket.

“Why a hotel?” Peter’s brow pulls down.

“Where is she going?” Harold looks around.

“Vegas.” Buck mutters. Realization dawns on Clint and Peter.

“Over my dead body.” He growls, heading for the door. Clint right on his heels, the others hurrying after them.

“Do we want to know about Vegas?” Harold asks as Clint unlocks the doors to his Four Runner.

“No.” Clint, Bucky and Peter grumble, everyone piling in. They’re speeding out of the clubhouse parking lot moments later.

“So you ended it with MJ?” Clint asks after several long minutes of silence. Nat and Bucky sat in the hatch, leaving Harold and Tony in the backseat.

“I don’t love her.” He sighs. “Besides, she cheated on me at her bachelorette party, and blackmailed your sister into leaving town. I couldn’t ever forgive her for that alone, I can’t marry her.” He shrugs a shoulder, looking out the window.

“You know when Y/N was graduating, I figured one of you was going to come clean.” Clint smirks, eyes on the road, as Peter looks over at him. “Then she said she wanted to go to Duke. I thought for damn sure your ass was going to go with her.” He nods slowly. “But I heard her crying that night, and you texted me about Felicia. I figured you two had a fight or something. You’d make up and come clean. Till we got those letters.” He sighs.

“I was trying to find away to tell you.” He admits. “I was going to beg her to stay here, to stay with me. Till Felicia came along ruining everything. She told Y/N I cheated. There was nobody but your sister, Clint. Nobody, still isn’t anyone else.” He shrugs, glancing out the window again.

“Well obviously, you picked her over the woman you were marrying.” Clint laughs, several chuckles come from the back of the truck.

“She isn’t Y/N.” He sighs, dropping his head back against the head rest. “Since she’s been back, I’ve been drowning like I’m eighteen again and dying for the smallest contact from her.” He smirks in the dark.

“I planned to object at your wedding.” Clint laughs. Peter’s head snaps over stunned.

“What?” He laughs.

“Me too.” Buck calls from the backseat. He looks back at them.

“Same.” Nat smirks.

“We planned to drug and kidnap you.” Tony jerks a thumb at Harold who nods.

“Yup.” He grins.

“So you all had a plan?” He looks back at Clint who laughs.

“Oh yeah we all had one. From the night of your bachelor party.” Clint snorts.

“You weren’t very subtle.” Buck laughs.

“He never was! Not once in his life when it came to my little sister was he ever subtle or smooth.” Clint cracks up.

“I mean, I got your sister.” Peter shrugs, grinning.

“That’s not saying much. Look what her mom settled for.” Tony laughs.

“Damn dad you going to take that?” Clint laughs. Peter’s cracking up in the passenger seat.

“Hey, he can say what he wants. I still got your mom.” Harold chuckles, a cocky smirk on his lips.

“This family is so fucking weird.” Clint shakes his head.

“Hey that’s the hotel.” Peter pats the dash pointing with his other hand.

“What’s the plan?” Nat asks as they all pile out.

“Who needs a plan?” Peter looks at her funny.

“Oh, okay.” She nods slowly.

“Told you. Never smooth or subtle.” Clint whispers. He gives Clint’s shoulder a shove, before he heads for the door. He heads for the front desk.

“How can I help you?” She smiles.

“A woman checked in here, with a card, under the name of Y/N Barton.” He nods.

“She’s my sister. We’re just worried about her. She took off without a word and her phones off.” Clint flashes his ID and a grin at her.

“Sure. She’s in room 217. Elevator to the right, second floor and go left.” She directs them with a smile.

“Thanks.” Clint winks at her, Peter sighs shaking his head.

“It’s like taking Tony out.” He mutters, pushing Clint towards the elevator.
